Class NucleotideVariations

java.lang.Object
  annotate.genome.NucleotideVariations
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable, Identity, LocalizedSequenceFeature
public final class NucleotideVariations
extends java.lang.Object
implements LocalizedSequenceFeature

Author:
jaschasilbermann A Nucleotid Variations object stores the information for a number of SNPs, all of which are at the same position in the genome and have the same rsID. The individual SNPs can be retrieved via the #next() method as long as #hasNext() returns true. Make sure to call #getIterator() before using these two methods!
